---------------------------------------------------------------------HTML5 and CSS----------------------------------------------------------------


Head Element -- Title,CSS styles, info for browser,search engine etc
Body Element -- Content, text ,links etc
Body can have headings -h1 to h6..h1 most important and h6 least

######HTML Elements############
1)Title
2)Headings - <h1></h1> (Headings are to highlight something.Can range from h1 to h6.h1 is biggest and h6 is smallest)
3)Paraghraphs - <p></p> (elemenst for larger text)
4)Bold element - <strong></strong>  (Anything inside these elements gets bold)
5)Italics element - <em></em>  (anything inside this will be in italics)
6)Underline - <u></u>  (anything inside this will be underlined)
7)Line break - <br>  (line break.no need for opening or closing this.just put br)
8)Images - <img src="" alt="text if image does not get loaded"> (no closing element needed for images tag)
9)Links - <a href="">link to google</a>   (this  open the link on thje same page you work)
<a href="" target="_blank">link to google</a> (target ="_black" this will open the link in a new tab).href="# means a dummy link which does nothing"
We can also link to other documents like images with this and not only the other websites
10)Link to style sheet - <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="style.css"> (rel tells browser its a stylesheet,type tells html its a css and href is the path to css.Link tag is also a standalone and does not need any closing)
11)Divison - Div
12)<header></header> (here you put logo,navigation,hero-image(big background image),main heading,button on images.It works like a regular div element.tells search engines some info)
13)
14)


#####CSS#######
3 ways to use
1)Style attribute
2)inside HTML document
3)inside .css file

CSS Properties
*Color - color:#123 , color:rgba(red,blue,green,visibility)
*Background-Image: - background-image(base image in background) 
*Background-size: cover(scale the image to cover background)
*Background-Position : center(image is at center)
*text-align:justify
*box-sizing : boerder-box
*margin:0;
*padding:0;
*display : table;
*clear: both;
*font-family: 'Arial'
*font-size: 300px ()
*font-weight: 300 (light to thick)
*letter-spacing: 1px(spaces between letters)
*word-spacing: 3px
*height: 100vh; (means it covers 100% of the view)
*transform : translate(-50% , -50%); (decreases top and left by 50%)
*display : block,inline,inline-block


Rules --selector and declaration box

h1{
	
}
Here h1 is the selector and curly brackets is the rules for all header1

Various attributes
1)Headings - color, font-size, font-family(Arial,Times new roman etc)
2)Paragraph - font-size,text-align :justify(),font-family
CSS inheritance - Child elements inherit the properties of parent elements unless we override their styles.

3)Color consist of color and transparency rgba(12,13,14,.75)
4)Classes and Id's in css
*For class css we use the . notation
.main-text{       (here main-text is the class for some element)
	text-align:justify
}

*For id's we use # symbol

#creator-text{   (here creator-text is the id of some element)
	
}

5)CSS Box model
*content(actual content),Padding(transparent area around the content),Border(goes around padding and content),margin(space between boxes).Padding,border and margin are properties incss and can be applied to any side of box.HEIGHT AND WIDTH ARE FOR ENTIRE BOX NOT FOR CONTENT.
*Block element span the whole width like paragraphs)and inline elements(cant set their hight or width.they end with the image).There is also inline-block..its like inline element but can have heading and margin.
*Asterisk selector is used to affect all elements and usully to remove defaults
*{
	margin:0;
	padding:0;
	box-sizing:border-box;   (With this the width and height properties includes content,padding and border but not the margin.If we do not include this then width and height are for the entire box.)
}

6)Layouts

First put everything in straight div from up to down, then assign width with % and make sure its 100% for the ones you want in line, then assign flout:left
{
	flout:left
}

clear property to counter float
.clearfix:after {    (:after does not have any space)
	content : "";
	display : table;
	clear: both;
}

*padding is inside the box remember so background color applies to padding as well whereas margin is outside the box.Box contains content and padding.

7)Absolute vs relative

Elements with absolute position can be positioned anywhere we want inside their parent.By default all elements are static positioned.
If you want to create an absolute position then parent should be relative.
position :relative
position :absolute

8)General tips
Use fond size between 15 to 25 around 20 px is good (fox regular text)
Headlines should be 50-70px...line spaceing should be 120%-150%
45-90 charachters is optimal (like around 80 is good)
Good fonts - Raleway,PT sans,Lato---google fonts website
Use single base color -- PETER RIVER,MIDNIGHT BLUE, ---Flat UI colors...use a color palette i.e a group of colors for website.Never use black color for design
Overlay the image with colors...image blur is also useful...floor fade (lower level of webside is darker)...get images from course ebook
Icons -icon fonts...get some free icon sets in ebook
put whitespace between elements,website sections etc.major sections have higher whitespace...
use fluid grid -- use percentages instead of px, use flexible imahes

